definition.value: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained via global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate.
A carboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any N-acylglycine.
Dianion of UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine arising from deprotonation of both free diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 4-oxobutanoic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A D-alpha-amino acid zwitterion that is D-proline in which a proton has been transferred from the carboxy group to the amino group. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
The dianion of any alpha-D-hexose 1-phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
An ionic phospholipid that is a dianion of a phosphatidic acid arising from deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups.
Zwitterionic form of guanidinoacetic acid having an anionic carboxy group and a protonated guanidino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of guanosine 3',5'-cyclic phosphate arising from deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.
The cationic sphingoid resulting from the protonation of the amino group of sphingosine.
A D-alpha-amino acid zwitterion that is D-threonine in which a proton has been transferred from the carboxy group to the amino group. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
An ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of pyridoxamine arising from selective protonation of the primary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Tetraanion of NADPH arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate and phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of CMP-N-acetyl-beta-neuraminate arising from deprotonation of carboxylic acid and phosphate functions; major species at pH 7.3.
A cationic sphingoid obtained by protonation of the amino group of sphinganine.
An ammonium ion that is the trication of spermidine, formed by protonation at all three nitrogens.
The heptaanion of a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of L-methionine having a anionic carboxy group and a cationic amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine arising from migration of a proton from the carboxy group to the alpha-amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of a nucleoside 5'-phosphate.
Zwitterionic form of 6-aminopenicillanic acid arising from migration of a proton from the carboxy group to the 6-amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol; major species at pH 7.3.
An  ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of tryptamine arising from protonation of the primary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A peptide anion obtained by deprotonation of both carboxy groups and protonation of the glutamyl amino group of glutathione; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of L-threonine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Trianion of nucleoside diphosphate arising from deprotonation of all three free OH groups of the diphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of D-methionine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of NADH arising from deprotonation of the two diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of creatine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the guanidino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 5-oxo-D-proline; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of L-saccharopine arising from deprotonation of all three carboxy groups and protonation of the primary and secondary amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of beta-alanine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the dianion of ADP-D-ribose(2-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
An ammonium ion that is the trication of hygromycin B arising from protonation of the three amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of the two carboxy groups of bilirubin; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of allysine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Dicarboxylate anion of biliverdin; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of a primary aliphatic amine.
Trication of streptomycin arising from protonation of the guanidino and secondary amino groups.
Pentaanion of 5-O-phosphono-alpha-D-ribofuranosyl diphosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The dianion of a nucleoside monophosphate: major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of L-asparagine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is a trianion arising from deprotonation of the carboxy and diphosphate OH groups of UDP-alpha-D-glucuronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A nucleoside 5'-monophosphate(2-) that results from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of IMP; major species at pH 7.3.
An amino acid zwitterion of homocysteine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A nucleoside 5'-diphosphate(3-) arising from deprotonation of the three triphosphate OH groups of cytidine 5'-diphosphate (CDP); major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of morphine arising from protonation of the tertiary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Trianion of nucleoside triphosphate arising from deprotonation of three of the four free triphosphate OH groups.
A nucleoside 5'-monophosphate(2-) that results from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of GMP.
